definitions.definition: A picture of a celebrity, an event etc., intended to be attached to a wall.
examples: He has posters of his favorite band, sports teams and holiday resorts up.

definitions.definition: An advertisement to be posted on a pole, wall etc. to advertise something.
examples: I saw a poster for the film on the side of a bus.

definitions.definition: ( Internet ) One who posts a message .
examples: Some posters left the online message board after the squabble.

definitions.definition: ( Australian rules football , informal ) A shot that hits a goalpost , scoring one point.
( ice hockey , slang ) A shot that hits a goalpost instead of passing into the goal .
examples: We got three posters in the third and lost.

definitions.definition: ( basketball ) A dunk over a defending player.
